# HypeVault frontend + Superpowers

## Scope

- Prefer **only** changes under `frontend/` unless the user explicitly asks for backend or full-stack work.

## Superpowers

- Official install: in **Cursor**, add the **Superpowers** plugin from the marketplace (or run `/add-plugin superpowers` in Agent chat). See https://github.com/obra/superpowers
- **Vendored copy** (offline reference): `vendor/superpowers/` — refresh with `npm run superpowers:bootstrap` from `frontend/`.
- For non-trivial UI work, follow Superpowers-style flow: clarify requirements → short plan → implement → verify (`npm run build`, manual checks in browser).

## Frontend conventions

- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, TanStack Query, Framer Motion.
- Design tokens: primary `#0A0A0A`, accent `#FF3B00`, success `#00C851`, danger `#FF3B30`, background `#F5F5F5`, cards `#FFFFFF`; radius 12px cards / 8px controls; 4px spacing baseline.
- Use project skills in `.cursor/skills/` when relevant (`price_dashboard.md`, `image_upload.md`, `authentication.md` for UI that touches those areas).
